{"content":[{"text":"Overview","type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"KeyboardKit has device-related features that can help customize your keyboard for various device types, orientations and screen sizes.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Although you should avoid targeting a specific device, orientation, or screen size, some keyboard features require these considerations.","type":"text"}]},{"text":"Device type","type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"Device-type"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"KeyboardKit has a platform-agnostic "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKitPro\/documentation\/KeyboardKitPro\/DeviceType","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" enum that defines available, supported device types."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"You can use ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKitPro\/documentation\/KeyboardKitPro\/DeviceType\/current","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" to get the current device type, then use properties like ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKitPro\/documentation\/KeyboardKitPro\/DeviceType\/isPhone","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" to determine what kind of device it is.","type":"text"}]},{"code":["let device = DeviceType.current","let isPhone = device.isPhone","let isPad = device.isPad"],"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing"},{"text":"Interface orientation","type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"Interface-orientation"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"KeyboardKit has a platform-agnostic "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKitPro\/documentation\/KeyboardKitPro\/InterfaceOrientation","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" enum that defines various interface (screen) orientations."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"You can use ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKitPro\/documentation\/KeyboardKitPro\/InterfaceOrientation\/current","type":"reference"},{"text":" to get the current interface orientation, then use properties like ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKitPro\/documentation\/KeyboardKitPro\/InterfaceOrientation\/isPortrait","type":"reference"},{"text":" to determine its orientation type:","type":"text"}]},{"code":["let orientation = InterfaceOrientation.current","let isPortrait = orientation.isPortrait","let isLandscape = orientation.isLandscape"],"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing"},{"anchor":"Screen-sizes","text":"Screen sizes","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"KeyboardKit has "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CGSize"},{"type":"text","text":" extensions for detecting which hardware you’re on, for instance to define and compare various screen sizes."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You can use "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"isScreenSize(_:withTolerance:)"},{"type":"text","text":" to check if a certain size matches a screen size in any orientation. It uses a low tolerance by default to support slight variations between model changes of the same device type."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Be careful with using screen size as the foundation for certain features. You never know if your software suddenly runs in another way that makes the screen size irrelevant, e.g. in iPad split screen or floating keyboard mode."}]}],"name":"Warning","type":"aside","style":"warning"}],"kind":"content"}],"metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"KeyboardKitPro"}],"roleHeading":"Article","title":"Device Utilities","role":"article","images":[{"type":"card","identifier":"Page.png"}]},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"This article describes the KeyboardKit device utilities."}],"references":{"doc://